        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer206441173" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6726578899255626397">How wonderfully freaked out is this book? It&apos;s about a young, introverted zen priest who becomes obssessed with a six hundred year old temple to the exclusion of everything else in his life, and then decides it has to be burned down to the ground. And it actually happened! Mishima is just brilliant at sucking you into the world of Mizoguchi&apos;s damaged neurosis. And almost every paragraph has at least one mind-fuck brilliant observation about beauty, ugliness, love, obsession, destruction, what ha</span>
  <span id="freeText6726578899255626397" style="display:none">How wonderfully freaked out is this book? It's about a young, introverted zen priest who becomes obssessed with a six hundred year old temple to the exclusion of everything else in his life, and then decides it has to be burned down to the ground. And it actually happened! Mishima is just brilliant at sucking you into the world of Mizoguchi's damaged neurosis. And almost every paragraph has at least one mind-fuck brilliant observation about beauty, ugliness, love, obsession, destruction, what have you. It's not exactly a novel, and not exactly a treatise on aesthetics, but some delerious hybrid of both. I feel like this book is an example of the exact right author finding the exact right story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6726578899255626397" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
